# ---- Rust / Cargo build output ----
# Compiled artifacts and intermediate build files for every crate in the workspace.
/target/
**/target/
# Older convention some tools still emit.
debug/

# Cargo.lock is intentionally NOT ignored: this workspace ships binaries (ftrio-cli -> `ftrio`,
# ftrio-playground -> `playground`), and the Rust guidance is to commit Cargo.lock for anything
# that produces an executable so builds are reproducible. If this were a pure library, you would
# uncomment the next line instead.
# Cargo.lock

# Backup files generated by rustfmt.
**/*.rs.bk

# Debug info emitted by MSVC builds of rustc/binaries.
*.pdb

# Expanded-macro / cargo-expand scratch output.
*.expanded.rs

# ---- Coverage / profiling ----
*.profraw
*.profdata
/coverage/
tarpaulin-report.*

# ---- Editors / IDEs ----
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml
# Vim / Emacs swap & backup files.
*.swp
*.swo
*~
\#*\#
.\#*

# rust-analyzer local cache (if configured to write into the tree).
.rust-analyzer/

# ---- OS cruft ----
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# ---- Local environment / secrets ----
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
